RE ENA DailyOops Sorry Original Message From Staab Theresa Sent Thursday November PM To Schlecht Dinah Subject RE ENA Daily I didnt see the attachment Original Message From Schlecht Dinah Sent Thursday November PM To Staab Theresa Felling Amy Subject ENA Daily Dinah L Schlecht Sr Market Services Rep Bear Paw Energy work cell

Wyoming Interstate Company WIC Maintenance Cc email email One unit at the Douglas Station on WIC will be out of service October for approximately hours Throughput for this period will be reduced to a rate of about MMcfd with a total daily throughput estimated at MMCfd As this will directly effect all gas coming out of the Powder River please contact your marketer directly as to how much gas they will be able to deliver into WIC on that day Allocations will be based on WIC allocation methods Dinah L Schlecht Sr Market Services Rep Bear Paw Energy work cell

OBA Imbalance Sheet Cc Scott Walt A couple of thingsI talked to Theresa today and the OBA Spreadsheet or actually Enrons imbalance sheet needs to be changed for both October and November as follows October ENA purchased mmbtud from Westport at the Bear Paw point beginning October We need to add a column on the ENA sheet ie similar to Phillips showing that mmbtu Quantum ENA did not purchase any gas from Quantum for October We had some measurement of gas from Quantum throughout the month This needs to go to imbalance between Quantum and Crestone November ENA is purchasing mmbtud from Quantum If Quantum produces more than mmbtud that extra goes to imbalance between Quantum and Crestone ENA is not purchasing Westports gas at this time I would be happy to make these changes but I am unsure as to how this file affects your Meter Allocation report and I dont want to mess that one up Im copying Theresa on this memoplease feel free to add to it if I missed something Thanks Dinah L Schlecht Sr Market Services Rep Bear Paw Energy work cell
Revised Enron Daily Email Nov xlsCitations nominated volume on Powder sheet revised

Wyoming Interstate Gas Company WIC Maintenance Cc email email On Tuesday November the Douglas Station will be out of service for approximately hours Throughput during the work will be reduced to a rate of about MMCfd with a total daily throughput estimated at MMcfd As this will directly effect all gas coming out of the Powder River please contact your marketer directly as to how much gas they will be able to deliver into WIC on that day Allocations will be based on WIC allocations methods Dinah L Schlecht Sr Market Services Rep Bear Paw Energy work cell
